mcp_support.registration_shape:
stdio (.mcp.json):
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "my-db": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@bytebase/dbhub", "--dsn", "postgresql://localhost/mydb"],
      "env": { "CACHE_DIR": "/tmp" }
    }
  }
}

http / streamable-http (with header + env expansion):
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "private-api": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "${API_BASE_URL:-https://api.example.com}/mcp",
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer ${API_KEY}" }
    }
  }
}

sse (deprecated) and ws use the same url/headers fields with "type": "sse" or "type": "ws".

CLI equivalents:
  claude mcp add --transport stdio --env KEY=val name -- npx -y server
  claude mcp add --transport http notion https://mcp.notion.com/mcp
  claude mcp add-json name '{"type":"stdio","command":"/path","args":[]}'
(--scope local|project|user controls destination; type "streamable-http" is accepted as an alias for "http".)

hooks_support.config_mechanism:
Declared as a "hooks" object in a settings.json file (NOT in .mcp.json). Locations/scopes: ~/.claude/settings.json (user, all projects), .claude/settings.json (project, committable), .claude/settings.local.json (project, gitignored), managed policy settings (org-wide), plugin hooks/hooks.json, and skill/agent frontmatter. Structure: each event key holds an array of groups, each group has an optional "matcher" (tool name / regex / event-specific value) and a "hooks" array of handlers. Handler "type" is one of: command (shell), http (POST to url), mcp_tool (call a connected MCP tool), prompt (single-turn LLM eval), agent (multi-turn subagent, experimental). Example:
{
  "hooks": {
    "PreToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Edit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          { "type": "command", "command": "\"$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR\"/.claude/hooks/protect-files.sh", "timeout": 30, "if": "Bash(git *)" }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PostToolUse": [
      { "matcher": "Edit|Write", "hooks": [{ "type": "command", "command": "jq -r '.tool_input.file_path' | xargs npx prettier --write" }] }
    ]
  }
}

Codex CLI has a hooks system (enabled by default; disable with [features] hooks = false). Hooks load from either a hooks.json file or an inline [hooks] table in config.toml, at user (~/.codex/), project (<repo>/.codex/, trusted only), system, managed/MDM, and plugin-bundled layers. The structure mirrors Claude Code's event -> [{matcher, hooks:[{type, command,...}]}] shape. Inline TOML example:
[[hooks.PreToolUse]]
matcher = "^Bash$"

[[hooks.PreToolUse.hooks]]
type = "command"
command = 'python3 script.py'
timeout = 30
statusMessage = "Checking command"

Equivalent ~/.codex/hooks.json:
{
  "hooks": {
    "PreToolUse": [
      { "matcher": "Bash", "hooks": [ { "type": "command", "command": "/usr/bin/python3 script.py", "timeout": 30, "statusMessage": "Checking command" } ] }
    ]
  }
}
A Windows-specific command variant can be supplied via commandWindows. Separately, the simpler notify = ["program", "args"] setting runs an external program on lifecycle events (currently agent-turn-complete).

mcp_support.registration_shape:
MCP servers go under the top-level "mcp" key, keyed by unique server name. The crucial distinction is type: "local" (stdio, uses command[]) vs type: "remote" (HTTP, uses url).

Local / stdio:
{
  "$schema": "https://opencode.ai/config.json",
  "mcp": {
    "my-local-server": {
      "type": "local",
      "command": ["npx", "-y", "my-mcp-command"],
      "enabled": true,
      "environment": { "MY_ENV_VAR": "value" }
    }
  }
}

Remote / http:
{
  "$schema": "https://opencode.ai/config.json",
  "mcp": {
    "my-remote-server": {
      "type": "remote",
      "url": "https://my-mcp-server.com",
      "enabled": true,
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer MY_API_KEY" }
    }
  }
}

Note: command is an array of [exe, ...args] (not separate command/args fields). enabled:false disables without removing. Optional timeout (ms). For remote, oauth is auto-detected on 401; set "oauth": false to disable, or pass an oauth object (clientId/clientSecret/scope) to override.

hooks_support.config_mechanism:
Plugin-based, not a JSON hook table. A plugin is a JS/TS module that EXPORTS an async function receiving a context object and RETURNING a hooks object keyed by hook name. Local plugins: drop .ts/.js files in .opencode/plugin/ (project) or ~/.config/opencode/plugin/ (global) and they auto-load at startup. NPM plugins: list package names in the top-level "plugin": ["pkg-name", "@org/pkg"] array in opencode.json (installed via Bun at startup, cached in ~/.cache/opencode/node_modules/). Context object provides { project, client, $ (Bun shell), directory, worktree }. Example:
export const EnvProtection = async ({ project, client, $, directory, worktree }) => ({
  "tool.execute.before": async (input, output) => {
    if (input.tool === "read" && output.args.filePath.includes(".env"))
      throw new Error("Do not read .env files")
  }
})

mcp_support.registration_shape:
TWO generations exist — verify which one your installed extension uses.

LEGACY format (.kilocode/mcp.json, Roo/Cline-style, top-level "mcpServers" key):
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "my-local-server": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "my-mcp-command"],
      "env": { "API_KEY": "your_api_key" },
      "disabled": false,
      "alwaysAllow": ["read_only_tool_name"]
    },
    "my-remote-server": {
      "type": "streamable-http",
      "url": "https://my-mcp-server.com/mcp",
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer MY_API_KEY" },
      "disabled": false,
      "alwaysAllow": []
    }
  }
}
(legacy local uses scalar "command" + separate "args"[] + "env"; remote uses type "sse" or "streamable-http".)

NEW format (kilo.jsonc, OpenCode-style, top-level "mcp" key):
{
  "mcp": {
    "my-local-server": {
      "type": "local",
      "command": ["npx", "-y", "my-mcp-command"],
      "environment": { "API_KEY": "your_api_key" },
      "enabled": true,
      "timeout": 10000
    },
    "my-remote-server": {
      "type": "remote",
      "url": "https://my-mcp-server.com/mcp",
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer MY_API_KEY" },
      "enabled": true,
      "timeout": 15000
    }
  }
}
Tool auto-approval in new format via top-level "permission": { "myserver_tool": "allow", "myserver_*": "allow" }.
